    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_RetrieveScenarioNamesByDEMChangeID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve scenario names from a view named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "budget.vwScenarios",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " based on a specific "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DEMChangeID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". It concatenates the scenario name with the fiscal year (FY) in parentheses and orders the results by fiscal year in descending order and by name in ascending order. The procedure uses a read-uncommitted transaction isolation level to minimize locking and blocking."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single SELECT statement with a simple WHERE clause and ORDER BY clause. It does not involve complex logic, multiple joins, or subqueries, making it low in complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@DEMChangeID AS INT",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This is the sole input parameter, representing the identifier for a specific DEM change. It is used to filter the scenarios in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "vwScenarios",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " view to return only those that match the given "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "DEMChangeID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SET NOCOUNT ON",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This command is used to prevent the message indicating the number of rows affected by a T-SQL statement from being returned. This can reduce network traffic and improve performance slightly."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This sets the isolation level to read uncommitted, allowing the procedure to read data that might be in the process of being modified by other transactions. This can reduce locking contention but at the risk of reading uncommitted or \"dirty\" data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SELECT Statement",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure selects the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Name",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " field from the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "vwScenarios",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " view, concatenates it with the fiscal year ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "FY",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "), and formats it as "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ScenarioName",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". The "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "WHERE",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " clause filters the records based on the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "DEMChangeID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ORDER BY Clause",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The results are ordered by fiscal year in descending order and by name in ascending order, ensuring that the most recent fiscal years appear first."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Read Uncommitted Isolation Level",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": While this reduces locking and can improve performance, it may lead to reading uncommitted data, which could be inconsistent or incorrect."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Indexing",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Performance can be significantly improved if there are appropriate indexes on the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "DEMChangeID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "FY",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Name",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " columns in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "vwScenarios",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " view. This would speed up the filtering and ordering operations."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Network Traffic",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SET NOCOUNT ON",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " helps reduce unnecessary network traffic by suppressing the \"rows affected\" message."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Dirty Reads",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The use of the READ UNCOMMITTED isolation level can lead to dirty reads, where the data read might not be committed and could be rolled back, leading to potential inconsistencies."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Integrity",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "vwScenarios",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " view is based on complex joins or aggregations, the use of READ UNCOMMITTED might lead to reading partial or inconsistent data sets."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Error Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure lacks error handling mechanisms. If an error occurs during execution, it will not be caught or logged, which could lead to unhandled exceptions."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Scalability",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": As the dataset grows, the performance might degrade if the view or underlying tables are not properly indexed, especially given the ordering requirements."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE PROCEDURE [input].[USP_RetrieveScenarioNamesByDEMChangeID]\n\t@DEMChangeID AS INT\r\nAS\r\nBEGIN\r\n\tSET NOCOUNT ON;\r\n\tSET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL READ UNCOMMITTED;\r\n\r\n\tSELECT [Name]  + ' (' + CONVERT(VARCHAR(4), FY) + ')'  AS ScenarioName\r\n\tFROM budget.vwScenarios\r\n\tWHERE DEMChangeID = @DEMChangeID\r\n\tORDER BY FY DESC, Name ASC;\r\nEND\r"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}